It questions the extent to which French political strategists (and the intellectual elite so fiercely defending secularism) are truly committed to pluralism.
He suggests that Muslims are likely to be treated more unfairly than Catholics, Protestants and Jews, who have also had to make their historic commitments to secular republicanism.
More than a growing pragmatism, it perceives “an adjustment of values.”
