The eviction represented an “unacceptable attack” on freedom of research and learning.
The exclusive focus on vandalism served to “delegitimize and criminalize protest” and diverted attention from content.
The Board of Directors has refused to enter into the necessary negotiations.
Teachers demand the immediate withdrawal of the legal claim.
Most of the occupants have not caused material damage, it is said.
Legitimized protest
The young people of the Verdi union and the German Federation of Trade Unions also stand in solidarity with the students.
The protest is a legitimate expression of a growing concern for one’s future, says Verdi’s national youth secretary Alexander Klein.
